# Hyperparameter Rationale

## Model Size (do NOT change without evidence)
- hidden_dim=256: right-sized for 60x12 input. 512 would 4x Transformer cost for marginal gain.
- 3 encoder layers: compositional depth for multi-step temporal reasoning. 2 loses depth, 4 adds cost.
- dim_feedforward=512: 2x hidden_dim is standard. Could try 256 for speed if training is slow.
- nhead=4: could experiment with 8 (zero param cost, finer attention) as a second-order optimization.

## RL Params
- gamma=0.99: minute-scale trades still benefit from looking ahead. 0.95 discounts too aggressively.
- batch_size=8192: balances GPU utilization (~41% VRAM on RTX 5090) with PER effectiveness. 16384 approximates uniform sampling.
- buffer=1M: 24k files x 1440 bars = 34M total bars. Larger buffer = more diverse replay.
- n_steps=3: tight credit assignment for in-and-out-in-minutes momentum. 5 was too long-horizon.
- reward_scale=1.0: with n_steps=3 and gamma=0.99, n-step returns stay in [-10, 10] C51 support. Old scale=10 caused edge-piling.

## Hardware Context (RTX 5090 + Ryzen 9 9950X3D)
- batch=8192 uses 13.3 GB / 31 GB VRAM (41.4%)
- Forward: 128ms, Backward: 1178ms at batch=8192
- Preprocessing 27k files: ~10 seconds with 12 CPU workers
- GPU is not the bottleneck; environment stepping is
